
[1]sieve

   SIEVE, n. siv. An utensil for separating flour from bran, or the fine
   part of any pulverized or fine substance from the coarse, by the hand;
   as a fine sieve; a coarse sieve. It consists of a hoop with a hair
   bottom, and performs in the family the service of a bolter in a mill.
